The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, April 27, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, April 27, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Ballygunge Phari to Park Circus. Dug up for tram track dereservation.				 																Screenings				 																																	Bhalo Theko, directed by Gautam Haldar, will be screened as part of Cinema in Celebration of Life at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm.				 																																	Screening of Gentlemen Prefer Blondes and documentaries The Studio System and The Star, at Nandan III, between 11.30 am and 4.30 pm. A discussion on Hollywood: yesterday, today and tomorrow will also be held as part of the programme presented by American Center and Calcutta University. By invitation only.				 																Talk				 																																	Bonani Kakkar will speak on Calcuttas Problems and Citizens Action at the CMA-Patton Tuesday Talkshoppe, at CMA Auditorium, at 5.45 pm.				 																On stage 				 																																	Mumbai-based theatre group Anandam will stage Dustu Projapati, organised by Bengal Chamber of Commerce and Industry, at Rabindra Sadan, 5.45 pm.				 																Workshops				 																																	A workshop on the Kushan folk dance of Assam, conducted by Sushmita Adhikari, at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, 6.30 pm.				 																																	Craftspersons from Assam, Bihar, Jharkhand, Orissa and West Bengal will conduct a workshop on wood carving at Aikatan, IA 290, Salt Lake, from 10 am to 5 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	Paintings by M.F.Husain, based on the film Meenaxi: Tale of 3 cities, on display at Galerie88, 3 pm to 7 pm.
